!!! Pillar future features

Pillar 70 saw some major refactorings and cleaning: it does not rely on Grease and Magritte anymore. 
Its architecture is a lot cleaner.

Still some things are missing. Here is a little list of features that we are working on or will begin soon:

- Incremental recompilation. Since we remove the use of make (so that Windows users can use Pillar), we should introduce a way to avoid recompiling the entire book when just one chapter changes
- Markdown syntax
- *Ecstatic>https://github.com/guillep/ecstatic* website generator. Create sites with Pillar markup, mustache templates, and Pharo plugins. We are working on a second version.
- Better table support

!!! Conclusion
Pillar is still in active development and it keeps improving. The current version of Pillar, and the version documented in this booklet, is 7.0. This booklet will be synchronised with future enhancements.